Reasoning: A system of two linear equations in the form $A_1x + B_1y = C_1$ $A_2x + B_2y = C_2$ has no solution if and only if the lines are parallel and distinct. This condition is mathematically expressed by: $$ rac{A_1}{A_2} =  rac{B_1}{B_2} 
