eq  rac{5}{10}$$  Step 1: Find the values of $a$ that make the slopes equal (i.e., $ rac{A_1}{A_2} =  rac{B_1}{B_2}$): $$ rac{a}{3} =  rac{1}{a+2}$$ Cross-multiply: $$a(a+2) = 3$$ $$a^2 + 2a = 3$$ $$a^2 + 2a - 3 = 0$$ Factor the quadratic equation: $$(a + 3)(a - 1) = 0$$ This yields two possible values for $a$: $a = 1$ or $a = -3$.  Step 2: Check the condition $ rac{B_1}{B_2} 
eq  rac{C_1}{C_2}$: We calculate the ratio of the constants: $ rac{C_1}{C_2} =  rac{5}{10} =  rac{1}{2}$.  Case 1: $a = 1$ Check the ratio of coefficients: $$ rac{A_1}{A_2} =  rac{1}{3}$$ $$ rac{B_1}{B_2} =  rac{1}{1+2} =  rac{1}{3}$$ Since $ rac{1}{3} =  rac{1}{3}$, the lines are parallel. Check the ratio of constants: $ rac{C_1}{C_2} =  rac{5}{10} =  rac{1}{2}$. Since $ rac{1}{3} 
